<!-- FAQ -->
<section id="faq" class="section-light">
  <div class="inner">
    <div class="s-label reveal" style="justify-content:center"><span>Common Questions</span></div>
    <h2 class="reveal" style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;font-size:clamp(2rem,3vw,2.8rem);font-weight:400;margin-bottom:.6rem;color:var(--text-on-light);text-align:center;transition-delay:.05s">Straight answers, <em style="font-style:italic;color:var(--blue)">no runaround.</em></h2>
    <p class="reveal" style="color:var(--text-on-light-dim);margin-bottom:3rem;font-size:.94rem;text-align:center;transition-delay:.08s">Questions we hear every week — answered plainly.</p>
    <div class="faq-wrap reveal" style="transition-delay:.1s">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="faq-q">Will getting pre-qualified hurt my credit score?<div class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></div></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Pre-qualification uses a soft pull — zero impact to your score. A hard inquiry only happens when you formally apply, and we'll ask your permission before initiating one. Multiple mortgage inquiries within a 45-day window are also treated as a single inquiry by the credit bureaus.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="faq-q">How much do I need for a down payment?<div class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></div></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Conventional loans start at 3%, FHA at 3.5%, and VA at 0%. Many buyers have more flexibility than they assume. We'll show you the real monthly payment difference at each down payment level so you can make the call with actual numbers in front of you.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="faq-q">Can I qualify if I'm self-employed?<div class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></div></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Yes. Self-employed borrowers typically need two years of personal and business tax returns, a year-to-date P&L, and business bank statements. We've structured approvals for LLCs, S-corps, freelancers, and mixed-income households that other lenders turned down.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="faq-q">Are your rates better than my bank's?<div class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></div></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Typically yes — because we're a wholesale broker, not a retail lender. Your bank only offers its own products. We shop rates across multiple wholesale lenders competing for your file. We'll put both quotes on the same page so you can compare them directly.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="faq-q">What's the difference between pre-qualification and pre-approval?<div class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></div></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Pre-qualification is an estimate based on what you tell us. Pre-approval is document-verified and carries real weight with sellers in California's competitive markets. We recommend reaching pre-approval before making offers — it's one of the strongest tools a buyer can have.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="faq-q">How do I know if refinancing makes sense right now?<div class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></div></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">We run a break-even analysis: total closing costs divided by monthly savings. If you plan to stay past that break-even point, the refi likely makes sense. We share this with every refi client before they decide — we'd rather you skip one that doesn't serve you.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="faq-q">What credit score do I need?<div class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></div></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Conventional loans generally require a 620 minimum. FHA can go as low as 580 with 3.5% down. VA has no official minimum, though lender overlays typically apply. Call us — we'll tell you honestly if there's a better time to apply and how to get there faster.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button type="button" class="faq-q">How long does closing actually take?<div class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg></div></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner">Our verified average is 21 days from complete application to funded loan. We track it because your agent, your seller, and your rate lock all depend on it. We'll give you a projected schedule on day one and flag anything that could affect it — early, not at the last minute.</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
